FuncDef:
The display ip netstream cache origin log command displays historical sampling information about NetStream IPv4 original flows on the CF card of a main control board based on 5-tuple information.
The display ipv6 netstream cache origin log command displays historical sampling information about NetStream IPv6 original flows on the CF card of a main control board based on 5-tuple information.
CLIs: display ip netstream cache origin [ source-ip <source-ip> ] [ source-port <source-port> ] [ destination-ip <destination-ip> ] [ destination-port <destination-port> ] [ protocol { udp | tcp | <protocol-number> } ] [ time-range from <start-time> to <end-time> ] log

display ipv6 netstream cache origin [ source-ipv6 <source-ipv6> ] [ source-port <source-port> ] [ destination-ipv6 <destination-ipv6> ] [ destination-port <destination-port> ] [ protocol { udp | tcp | <protocol-number> } ] [ time-range from <start-time> to <end-time> ] log

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies a source IPv4 address.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies a source port.
The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 65535 .

Specifies a destination IPv4 address.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies a destination port.
The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 65535.

Specifies a protocol number.
The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 255.

Specifies the start time.
The value is in the format of YYYY/MM/DD,HH:MM:SS.
YYYY-MM-DD indicates the year/month/day.
The value of YYYY ranges from 1970 to 9999;
the value of MM ranges from 1 to 12; the value of DD ranges from 1 to 31.
HH:MM:SS indicates the hour:minute:second.
The value of HH ranges from 0 to 23; the value of MM and SS ranges from 0 to 59.

Specifies the end time.
The value is in the format of YYYY/MM/DD,HH:MM:SS.
YYYY-MM-DD indicates the year/month/day.
The value of YYYY ranges from 1970 to 9999;
the value of MM ranges from 1 to 12; the value of DD ranges from 1 to 31.
HH:MM:SS indicates the hour:minute:second.
The value of HH ranges from 0 to 23; the value of MM and SS ranges from 0 to 59.

Specifies a source IPv6 address.
The value is a 32-bit hexadecimal number, in the format of X:X:X:X:X:X:X:X.

Specifies a destination IPv6 address.
The value is a 32-bit hexadecimal number, in the format of X:X:X:X:X:X:X:X.

Examples: <HUAWEI> display ip netstream cache origin protocol udp log
<HUAWEI> display ipv6 netstream cache origin protocol udp log
ExtraInfo: NetStream sampling can be used to write aged sample original flows into the CF card of a main control board. To query historical sampling information about original flows on the CF card of the main control board based on 5-tuple information, run the display ip netstream cache origin log command or display ipv6 netstream cache origin log command.
